# Architectural Rules

- **Decoupled Artifact Pattern:** Do not pass large data structures exclusively in memory. Every pipeline stage must read from and write distinct, immutable JSON or media artifacts to disk.
- Never commit generated pipeline artifacts (e.g., .wav, .json timestamps, .mp4, or data/workspace/ contents) to version control.
- **No External APIs:** Avoid external APIs when adding new features or polish to the pipeline. Rely on local processing.
- AI orchestration uses a local instance of Gemma 4 12B Unified accessed via llama-cpp-python with strict JSON grammar enforcement.
